{% extends "static-base.html.template" %}
{% load i18n %}

{% block content %}
<h1>Information for responders</h1>

Any time Google launches Google Person Finder in response to a crisis,
government and nonprofit organizations can help people locate each other
by spreading the word, using the data, and adding information.

<div class="section">
<img class="inset" src="{{env.fixed_static_url_base}}/embed-80x57.png"
    width="80" height="57" alt="Embed Person Finder">
<h2>Embed Google Person Finder in your site</h2>

<p>
Spread the word about Google Person Finder to your community.
You can point people to
<a href="https://google.org/personfinder">this Google Person Finder page</a>,
or you can embed a small version of Google Person Finder
directly on your website using the following HTML code:

<pre>
&lt;iframe
    src="https://google.org/personfinder/<var>repository</var>/?ui=small"
    width=400 height=300 frameborder=0
    style="border: dashed 2px #77c"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
</pre>

<p>
(Replace <var>repository</var> with the appropriate repository name.)

<p>
The above gadget code is made available under the Apache 2.0 license,
and any data you receive in connection with the gadget
is shared under a Creative Commons license.
</div>

<div class="section">
<img class="inset" src="{{env.fixed_static_url_base}}/download-80x99.png"
    width="80" height="99" alt="Download data">
<h2>Download data from Google Person Finder</h2>

<p>
You can download the data in Google Person Finder
or synchronize it with your own database using the Google Person Finder API.
The information is provided in
People Finder Interchange Format (PFIF), which is based on XML.
See the 
<a href="https://github.com/google/personfinder/wiki/DataAPI">
Person Finder code site</a>
for detailed instructions on requesting access and downloading data.
</div>

<div class="section">
<img class="inset" src="{{env.fixed_static_url_base}}/upload-80x127.png"
    width="80" height="127" alt="Upload data">
<h2>Upload data into Google Person Finder</h2>

<p>
Add information from your database to Google Person Finder
to make it available to the public
and get the crowd to add what they know to the records.
You will need to format your data in
People Finder Interchange Format (PFIF)
in order to upload it into Google Person Finder.
See the 
<a href="https://github.com/google/personfinder/wiki/DataAPI">
Person Finder code site</a>
for detailed instructions on requesting access and uploading data.
</div>
{% endblock content %}
